description.narrative: In consultation with MOH, UNICEF generated evidence on KAPs of the community for use in planning for community engagement. This has been reflected in the AWPs, strategy and guideline development, and health staff training at different levels, such as training on EPI, C4D material development, and development and emergency response interventions. Approximately >6 million people reached with COVID 19 messages through multimedia. Overall, 16 million have been reached so far with activities on sharing foods, handwashing, community dialogue, and in participating phone-in programs and conferences. Over nearly 400,000 people have been engaged in various RCCE actions. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
